The paper focuses on analyzing the research output related to Sustainable Development Goals, which is a multidisciplinary topic. The paper uses bibliometric analysis to map the global research of sustainability goals, which involves data analysis and information retrieval techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
